    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-08T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-12-08T18:00:00-05:00" n="1652"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1652">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.8571/11–2149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">McConaughy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-12-08T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 8, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2391. Stated urtel 4862 Nov 21 “Shanghai not yet faced problem registration
                    property”. Have Commie auths Shanghai issued reg[ulation]s re registration
                    property? If so or if auths shld do so, Dept assumes ConGen will tele
                    translation text regs.</p>
                <p>For ur info Dept has instructed ConGens Tientsin Peiping,<note n="61"
                        xml:id="d1652fn61">See telegram No. 764, November 2, 5 p.m., <ref
                            target="#pg_1113">p. 1113</ref>.</note> in connection with Commie regs
                    requiring registration real property of aliens those cities by certain dates,
                    transmit to local Commie auths statement reserving rights absentee Amer owners
                    real property. Dept has issued press releases giving this info.<note n="62"
                        xml:id="d1652fn62">See Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>,
                        November 21, 1949, p. 760; November 1949, p. 800; December 5, 1949, p. 868a;
                        December 26, 1949, p. 957.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
